'From Squeak2.8alpha of 13 January 2000 [latest update: #2076] on 8 May 2000 at 3:36:05 pm'!"Change Set:		sampleInstance-swDate:			8 May 2000Author:			Scott WallaceFleshes out the 'make new instance from browser' feature introduced in update 2071:* The feature is now called 'sample instance'.* It is available in message-list menus as well as in class-list menus.* It is made robust."!!CodeHolder methodsFor: 'as yet unclassified' stamp: 'sw 5/8/2000 12:38'!makeSampleInstance	| aClass nonMetaClass anInstance |	(aClass _ self selectedClassOrMetaClass) ifNil: [^ self].	nonMetaClass _ aClass theNonMetaClass.	anInstance _ self sampleInstanceOfSelectedClass.	(anInstance isNil and: [nonMetaClass ~~ UndefinedObject]) ifTrue: 		[^ self inform: 'Sorry, cannot make an instance of ', nonMetaClass name].	(Smalltalk isMorphic and: [anInstance isMorph])		ifTrue:			[self currentHand attachMorph: anInstance]		ifFalse:			[anInstance inspectWithLabel: 'An instance of ', nonMetaClass name]! !!CodeHolder methodsFor: 'as yet unclassified' stamp: 'sw 5/8/2000 12:34'!sampleInstanceOfSelectedClass	| aClass |	"Return a sample instance of the class currently being pointed at"	(aClass _ self selectedClassOrMetaClass) ifNil: [^ nil].	^ aClass theNonMetaClass initializedInstance! !!False class methodsFor: 'as yet unclassified' stamp: 'sw 5/8/2000 11:09'!initializedInstance	^ false! !!Integer class methodsFor: 'instance creation' stamp: 'sw 5/8/2000 11:05'!initializedInstance	^ 2468! !!LargePositiveInteger class methodsFor: 'testing' stamp: 'sw 5/8/2000 12:05'!initializedInstance	^ 12345678901234567 copy! !!LargeNegativeInteger class methodsFor: 'as yet unclassified' stamp: 'sw 5/8/2000 12:05'!initializedInstance	^ -9876543210987654321 copy! !!True class methodsFor: 'as yet unclassified' stamp: 'sw 5/8/2000 11:09'!initializedInstance	^ true! !CodeHolder removeSelector: #makeNewInstance!